Make Nyxt's renderer signal handlers robust to FFI type-errors.

Newer WebKitGTK 2.5x and GDK 3.24.x sometimes hand stale or
not-yet-translated values to the renderer signal handlers, surfacing
as

  Warning: Error on GTK thread:
    The value 1073741824 is not of type GDK:GDK-EVENT
    when binding NYXT/RENDERER/GTK::EVENT

(see Guix bug #79119, Codeberg guix/guix#518).  When this signal
handler is invoked from a foreign thread, the resulting type-error
unwinds through SBCL's deferrable-signals machinery and can produce a
"fatal error encountered ... deferrable signals partially blocked"
abort that takes the whole renderer down (the page becomes blank and
the app is unusable).

Wrap the body of `connect-signal` and `connect-signal-function`'s
generated lambdas with `handler-case` so a single stray event from a
foreign thread cannot tear down the renderer.  This is intentionally
lossy: dropping one event is far better than killing the whole
session.  Once cl-cffi-gtk learns the new GDK enums upstream this
patch can be reverted.

--- a/source/renderer/gtk.lisp	2026-04-27 00:35:50.934774490 +0000
+++ b/source/renderer/gtk.lisp	2026-04-27 00:35:50.984774476 +0000
@@ -410,8 +410,11 @@
   "Connect SIGNAL to OBJECT with a function FN.
 OBJECT must have the `gtk-object' and `handler-ids' slots.
 See also `connect-signal'."
-  `(let ((handler-id (gobject:g-signal-connect
-                      (gtk-object ,object) ,signal ,fn)))
+  `(let* ((wrapped-fn (lambda (&rest args)
+                        (handler-case (apply ,fn args)
+                          (error (c) (declare (ignore c)) nil))))
+          (handler-id (gobject:g-signal-connect
+                       (gtk-object ,object) ,signal wrapped-fn)))
      (push handler-id (handler-ids ,object))))
 
 (defmacro connect-signal (object signal new-thread-p (&rest args) &body body)
@@ -426,11 +429,13 @@
                         (lambda (,@args)
                           ,@(sera:unsplice documentation)
                           ,@declares
-                          ,(if new-thread-p
-                               `(run-thread "renderer signal handler"
-                                    ,@forms)
-                               `(with-protect ("Error in signal on renderer thread: ~a" :condition)
-                                  ,@forms))))))
+                          (handler-case
+                              ,(if new-thread-p
+                                   `(run-thread "renderer signal handler"
+                                        ,@forms)
+                                   `(with-protect ("Error in signal on renderer thread: ~a" :condition)
+                                      ,@forms))
+                            (error (c) (declare (ignore c)) nil))))))
        (push handler-id (handler-ids ,object)))))
 
 (defmethod customize-instance :after ((window gtk-window) &key)
